title: Mediabridge Cat5e Ethernet Patch Cable (15 Feet) - RJ45 Computer Networking Cord - Red
description: Mediabridge Cat5e Ethernet Patch CableConnects a computer to a printer, router, switch box or other network component in a wired Local Area Network (LAN). Share server files, use a network printer, stream audio/video, link PC's through a network switch & more, at data transfer speeds up to 1000 Mbps (1 Gbps). This 24 AWG cable meets stricter TIA/EIA standards than normal Cat5 cables, & handles high-bandwidth needs. 50-micron male RJ45 connectors are built with corrosion-resistant gold-plating for high-quality accuracy. Noise, interference & crosstalk are reduced with its 4 unshielded twisted pairs (4PR UTP) of copper strands & tough, yet flexible PVC jacket. A heavy-duty, snag-less molding makes setup simple & 350 MHz bandwidth allows for high-speed distribution of data, voice & video.Product Features- Connects network components in a wired LAN at data transmission speeds up to 1 Gbps- 24 AWG cable exceeds TIA/EIA standards & 350 MHz bandwidth- 50-micron male RJ45 connectors per end, with corrosion-resistant gold-plating- 4PR UTP copper strands for minimal noise, interference & crosstalk- Tough, yet flexible PVC jacket & heavy-duty, snag-less moldCompatibility- Devices with RJ45 jacks, including computers & peripherals like routers, switch boxes, network printers & network attached storage devices- Cat5 is a computer networking standard & works with 10/100 Base-T networksInstallationPlug-&-play: Ready to use, once each end is connected to a respective port on a compatible deviceNotes- Network speed is determined by factors other than just cables, like a router/switch box- Also known as a network cable, computer cable, Category5e cable, Ethernet cable, or Data/LAN cableWarrantyLimited 1 Year WarrantySupportCall us Mon-Sat 9AM-6PM Eastern (extended hours Tue/Thu until 9PM).
